26/10/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The new head of the Serbia-Montenegro Armed Forces' General Staff, General Ljubisa Jokic, officially assumed his duties after a hand-over ceremony Tuesday (25 October). 
The Montenegrin general succeeds Dragan Paskas in the post. 
He pledged that reforms within the federal defence sector would continue.
Also Tuesday, the Montenegrin Parliament approved the nomination of Deputy Prime Minister Jusuf Kalaperovic as the republic's new interior minister. 
He replaces Dragan Djurovic. 
Local media is also reporting significant changes among leaders of the police. 
(Dan - 26/10/05; Beta, Tanjug - 25/10/05)
